        "comments": [
          {
            "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/13003433/comment/15472701",
            "id": "15472701",
            "author": {
              "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=varun_saxena",
              "name": "varun_saxena",
              "key": "varun_saxena",
              "avatarUrls": {
                "48x48": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452",
                "24x24": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452",
                "16x16": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452",
                "32x32": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"
              },
              "displayName": "Varun Saxena",
              "active": true,
              "timeZone": "Asia/Kolkata"
            },
            "body": "As discussed in call we can still serve this use case by allowing flow context information to be passed in TimelineEntity and take it if supplied to make writes to different tables.\n\nBut we also need to devise a mechanism to distribute writes to different collectors for such a use case.\n\nThis JIRA has been opened with the intention to discuss more on this.",
            "updateAuthor": {
              "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=varun_saxena",
              "name": "varun_saxena",
              "key": "varun_saxena",
              "avatarUrls": {
                "48x48": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452",
                "24x24": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452",
                "16x16": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452",
                "32x32": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"
              },
              "displayName": "Varun Saxena",
              "active": true,
              "timeZone": "Asia/Kolkata"
            },
            "created": "2016-09-08T04:20:41.972+0000",
            "updated": "2016-09-08T04:20:41.972+0000"
          },
          {
            "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/13003433/comment/15473212",
            "id": "15473212",
            "author": {
              "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=rohithsharma",
              "name": "rohithsharma",
              "key": "rohithsharma",
              "avatarUrls": {
                "48x48": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452",
                "24x24": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452",
                "16x16": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452",
                "32x32": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"
              },
              "displayName": "Rohith Sharma K S",
              "active": true,
              "timeZone": "America/New_York"
            },
            "body": "Does idea is to publish entities with single applicationId belongs to multiple flows?",
            "updateAuthor": {
              "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=rohithsharma",
              "name": "rohithsharma",
              "key": "rohithsharma",
              "avatarUrls": {
                "48x48": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452",
                "24x24": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452",
                "16x16": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452",
                "32x32": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"
              },
              "displayName": "Rohith Sharma K S",
              "active": true,
              "timeZone": "America/New_York"
            },
            "created": "2016-09-08T08:33:42.640+0000",
            "updated": "2016-09-08T08:33:42.640+0000"
          },
          {
            "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/13003433/comment/15473270",
            "id": "15473270",
            "author": {
              "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=varun_saxena",
              "name": "varun_saxena",
              "key": "varun_saxena",
              "avatarUrls": {
                "48x48": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452",
                "24x24": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452",
                "16x16": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452",
                "32x32": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"
              },
              "displayName": "Varun Saxena",
              "active": true,
              "timeZone": "Asia/Kolkata"
            },
            "body": "This is primarily for taking forward the discussion we had in last call i.e. with regards to Spark and Tez. To support one AM publishing entities of different flows/users.\nWe also need to support off-application entity publishing, a JIRA which you are working on.\n\nAnyways for former, I think we can publish flow information in entity and use it while writing data to tables.\nBut we also need to distribute workload across multiple collectors which cannot be done currently as collectors are based on apps.\n\nAs discussed in call, we can bring in a notion of sub-applications and limit number of node collectors per app to achieve this.\nIts still in discussion phase though and further suggestions are welcome. We can try to reach a conclusion on this by our next call.",
            "updateAuthor": {
              "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=varun_saxena",
              "name": "varun_saxena",
              "key": "varun_saxena",
              "avatarUrls": {
                "48x48": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452",
                "24x24": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452",
                "16x16": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452",
                "32x32": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"
              },
              "displayName": "Varun Saxena",
              "active": true,
              "timeZone": "Asia/Kolkata"
            },
            "created": "2016-09-08T08:53:37.026+0000",
            "updated": "2016-09-08T08:53:37.026+0000"
          },
          {
            "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/13003433/comment/15520939",
            "id": "15520939",
            "author": {
              "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=jrottinghuis",
              "name": "jrottinghuis",
              "key": "jrottinghuis",
              "avatarUrls": {
                "48x48": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452",
                "24x24": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452",
                "16x16": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452",
                "32x32": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"
              },
              "displayName": "Joep Rottinghuis",
              "active": true,
              "timeZone": "America/Los_Angeles"
            },
            "body": "As per our discussion on the status call last week, it is very confusing to use the term \"flows\" in the description in \"its not possible for us to differentiate different flows.\nWhen flow here doesn't mean the same as flow in flow-run table. A flow is a set of applications that belong together.\n\nI think what is meant here is different queries and we discussed to see if we can introduce a concept of sub-application for this purpose.\nAlso part of the discussion was if we can store these sub-applications (I'll stick with that term for now) with a completely different row-key or even different table. It is good to keep in mind that the existing row-keys were designed such that each ats writer (except for the one serving the RM) has only 1 connection to 1 region server (by and large, ignoring region splits) for 1 table. If we're going to be writing to different users' and possibly queue prefix keys, then an ATS will have to make up to one new connection per query.\nThe entire idea why a Tez app, or a Scalding app has to start a long-running AM is to avoid the overhead of spinning up individual AMs. Logically that makes sense if there are many short-lived queries fired at the app. That is exactly the de-generate case when we'd have to take a hit on the ats writer side to connect to different region servers for each of these very short-lived queries. That doesn't seem to make much sense.\n\nIn general I'm wondering how in any larger production environment people are going to have a single (or pool of) Tez am(s) launched as one user, and then fire queries at it from a different user. How would one account for the wait time (am sitting around doing nothing?) who would get \"charged\" for that? If a group of users feel it is worth to spend these resources in order to get very quick interactive query responses, then that should be charged to the owner of the application launched.\n\nIf we introduce a post-fix for application so that we can have users grab the data for just one query, could that work?\n\nPerhaps we can even model this as different entities for the different queries can do the trick.\n\nEspecially complicating will be to have different queries run in different queues. I think we have a few assumptions that an application maps to 1 queue. We had an open item wrt. that queue changing over time, at which point offline aggregation will have to deal with correctly apportioning the various cost components to each appropriate queue.",
            "updateAuthor": {
              "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=jrottinghuis",
              "name": "jrottinghuis",
              "key": "jrottinghuis",
              "avatarUrls": {
                "48x48": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452",
                "24x24": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452",
                "16x16": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452",
                "32x32": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"
              },
              "displayName": "Joep Rottinghuis",
              "active": true,
              "timeZone": "America/Los_Angeles"
            },
            "created": "2016-09-25T14:53:03.924+0000",
            "updated": "2016-09-25T14:53:03.924+0000"
          },
          {
